  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ACCOUNTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p>· Manage full sets of accounts including AP, AR, GL, and bank reconciliations.</p><p>· Prepare accurate monthly financial and management reports, including P&L statements and cash flow forecasts.</p><p>· Track and reconcile daily sales data from POS systems.</p><p>· Handle supplier invoicing, payments, and liaise with vendors.</p><p>· Ensure compliance with statutory requirements such as GST, and annual audit support.</p><p>· Assist with budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis.</p><p>· Maintain proper documentation and records for audit and compliance.</p><p>· Use Xero to maintain up-to-date financial records and reports.</p><p>· Coordinate with internal teams and outlet managers to ensure timely financial inputs.</p><p>· Visit outlets when required.</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>· Diploma or Degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.</p><p>· Minimum 2–3 years of relevant experience, preferably in the F&B or hospitality industry.</p><p>· Proficient in Xero Accounting Software.</p><p>· Strong knowledge of Singapore financial regulations and GST reporting.</p><p>· Excellent attention to detail, time management, and organizational skills.</p><p>· Able to work independently and handle multiple priorities.</p><p>· Strong communication skills to work across departments.</p><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p><p>· Experience in multi-outlet or group accounting.</p><p>· Able to start immediately or within short notice.</p>",
